def: An etching or a print from an etched plate.
A genus of small insectivores including the common Europeanmole.
A genus of plant-eating beetles, including the potato beetle.See Potato beetle.

An instrument for measuring the quantity of dew on the surfaceof a body in the open air. It consists of a balance, having a plateat one end to receive the dew, and at the other a weight protectedfrom the deposit of dew.
A whitish marble, from Rome, containiing pale greenish zones.It consists of calcium carbonate, with zones and cloudings of talc.
A substance resembling, and isomeric with, ordinary camphor,and extracted from the essential oil of feverfew; -- called alsoPyrethrum camphor.
The act of overseeing; inspection; superintendence; oversight.
Sparing; chary. [Obs.] Fairfax.-- Spare"ful*ness, n. [Obs.] Sir P. Sidney.
Of or pertaining to the island anciently called Lesbos, nowMitylene, in the Grecian Archipelago.
The office, occupation, or persom of a pimp. [R.]
Like a lob; consisting of lobs. Sir. P. Sidney.
An active principle of Arnica montana. It is a bitter resin.
